stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Initialize: ralph run --config loop.toml "objective"

    Initialize --> LoadState: Check for existing state
    LoadState --> FreshStart: No state file found
    LoadState --> ResumeFromCheckpoint: State file exists\n(resume_on_start = true)

    FreshStart --> ReadContext: Create initial state
    ResumeFromCheckpoint --> ReadContext: Restore iteration counter,\ncurrent hat, task progress

    state IterationLoop {
        ReadContext --> SelectHat: Load specs, plans,\nmemories, guidance
        SelectHat --> ExecuteHat: Coordinator picks hat\nbased on event bus
        ExecuteHat --> BackpressureGates: Agent works in\nhat-scoped context

        BackpressureGates --> GatePass: All gates pass\n(build, lint, test)
        BackpressureGates --> GateFail: Gate failed

        GateFail --> ExecuteHat: Agent must fix\nand retry

        GatePass --> CheckpointDecision: Iteration complete
        CheckpointDecision --> WriteCheckpoint: iteration % interval == 0
        CheckpointDecision --> CheckCompletion: Not checkpoint iteration

        WriteCheckpoint --> PersistState: Atomic write to\nloop-state.json
        PersistState --> NotifyTelegram: Send checkpoint\nnotification
        NotifyTelegram --> CheckCompletion

        CheckCompletion --> StopHookCheck: Check if work remains
    end

    state StopHookDecision <<choice>>
    StopHookCheck --> StopHookDecision: stop-hook.sh runs

    StopHookDecision --> ReadContext: Tasks remain\n"The boulder never stops"
    StopHookDecision --> KillSignal: kill.signal detected
    StopHookDecision --> PauseState: pause.flag detected
    StopHookDecision --> Complete: All tasks done

    KillSignal --> [*]: Force terminate
    PauseState --> [*]: Pause (resume later)
    Complete --> FinalState: Write final state

    FinalState --> [*]: Loop complete\n(notify Telegram)

    note right of PersistState
        State includes:
        - iteration count
        - current_hat
        - task_progress
        - memory_snapshot
        - cost_accumulator
        Written atomically via
        tmp file + rename
    end note
